{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 02:35:33.516512", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nScope and Topology\\n- Environment: Multi-tier EBGP Clos (fat-tree) using FRR. Each leaf advertises its /24 host subnet; inter-router links use 172.16.0.0/16 /31s.\\n- Devices in focus: pc_0_0 (10.0.0.2/24 via leaf_router_0_0), pc_0_1 (10.0.1.2/24 via leaf_router_0_1), leaf_router_0_0 (10.0.0.1/24 on eth8), leaf_router_0_1 (10.0.1.1/24 on eth8), spines and super-spine.\\n\\n1) Anomaly Detection\\n- End-to-end reachability tests indicate a singular deviation centered on pc_0_0:\\n  - get_reachability shows status unknown/timeouts for traffic sourced from pc_0_0, while numerous other hosts show 0% loss and normal RTTs.\\n  - pc_0_0 cannot ping its own default gateway 10.0.0.1 (100% loss).\\n  - In contrast, pc_0_1 (and other hosts) exhibit normal connectivity to remote destinations and can ping 10.0.0.1 successfully.\\n\\n2) Fault Localization\\n- The failure is localized to the L3 adjacency between pc_0_0 and its leaf (leaf_router_0_0, interface eth8):\\n  - pc_0_0:\\n    - IP/route: 10.0.0.2/24, default via 10.0.0.1 (correct).\\n    - ARP: 10.0.0.1 has a resolved MAC (5a:16:34:1f:6e:99), indicating L2/ARP is working.\\n    - Ping to 10.0.0.1 fails 100% loss.\\n  - leaf_router_0_0:\\n    - Interface eth8 is up with 10.0.0.1/24.\\n    - ARP for 10.0.0.2 exists (STALE), but attempts to ping 10.0.0.2 return “Invalid argument”; ip route get 10.0.0.2 returns “RTNETLINK answers: Invalid argument.”\\n    - Kernel routing table contains a blackhole route for 10.0.0.0/24:\\n      - ip route shows: “blackhole 10.0.0.0/24” and also a connected route “10.0.0.0/24 dev eth8”.\\n      - ip -d route show 10.0.0.0/24 displays the blackhole; ip route get 10.0.0.2 fails.\\n    - FRR BGP on leaf_router_0_0 is healthy (8 eBGP peerings up; routes learned and installed). FRR’s own RIB shows both the blackhole and the connected 10.0.0.0/24, with the connected selected (>*) — but the Linux kernel FIB still contains the blackhole entry.\\n  - leaf_router_0_1 (reference/good state):\\n    - No blackhole for its local 10.0.1.0/24. pc_0_1 can ping 10.0.0.1 successfully, confirming leaf_router_0_0 responds to off-subnet ICMP and its upstream fabric is normal.\\n\\n3) Root Cause Identification\\n- Root cause: An erroneous kernel blackhole route exists on leaf_router_0_0 for the directly connected subnet 10.0.0.0/24.\\n  - Evidence:\\n    - ip route on leaf_router_0_0 shows “blackhole 10.0.0.0/24 proto boot scope global,” indicating a boot-time/static insertion outside of FRR.\\n    - Despite FRR selecting the connected 10.0.0.0/24 as best, the kernel FIB has the blackhole route present and effectively used for traffic resolution to 10.0.0.2 (ip route get fails; ping to 10.0.0.2 yields EINVAL).\\n    - pc_0_0 has valid ARP for 10.0.0.1 and sends ICMP echoes, but replies from the leaf to 10.0.0.2 are dropped by the blackhole route.\\n  - Scope of impact: All hosts on 10.0.0.0/24 attached to leaf_router_0_0 are impacted (pc_0_0 in this lab). Inbound traffic from the fabric towards 10.0.0.0/24 would also be discarded at the leaf due to the blackhole, while the leaf continues to advertise 10.0.0.0/24 via BGP (potential blackhole to the rest of the fabric).\\n  - Control plane health: eBGP sessions across the fabric (including both leaves) are up; RIBs show expected inter-pod prefixes. No evidence of BGP/session instability.\\n\\nKey Evidence Snippets\\n- pc_0_0:\\n  - ip route: default via 10.0.0.1 dev eth0\\n  - Ping 10.0.0.1: 100% packet loss\\n  - ARP: 10.0.0.1 ether 5a:16:34:1f:6e:99 C (complete)\\n- leaf_router_0_0:\\n  - ip neigh dev eth8: 10.0.0.2 lladdr ee:c3:5b:bf:73:67 STALE\\n  - ip route (partial): blackhole 10.0.0.0/24; 10.0.0.0/24 dev eth8 proto kernel\\n  - Ping 10.0.0.2: “ping: connect: Invalid argument”\\n  - ip route get 10.0.0.2: “RTNETLINK answers: Invalid argument”\\n  - FRR show ip route (partial): K * 10.0.0.0/24 unreachable (blackhole) and C>* 10.0.0.0/24 is directly connected, eth8\\n- pc_0_1:\\n  - Ping 10.0.0.1: success (proves leaf_router_0_0 is reachable and responds from off-subnet)\\n\\nConclusion\\n- Abnormal behavior is confined to the 10.0.0.0/24 access network on leaf_router_0_0.\\n- Faulty device/function: leaf_router_0_0 kernel FIB for the access VLAN/subnet.\\n- Root cause: Presence of a boot-time/static blackhole route for 10.0.0.0/24 (proto boot) on leaf_router_0_0, which overrides/prevents correct forwarding to directly connected host 10.0.0.2, isolating pc_0_0 from the network despite healthy BGP and upstream connectivity., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='7ce2ecd2-665b-4292-b725-c9e791b5b5a3'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
